{
  "texts": [
    "Following the case studies presented in Figure 4 and Figure 5, we provide numerical results on how GNN-RAG improves multi-hop question answering and how retrieval augmentation (RA) enhances simple hop questions.",
    "Table 9 summarizes these results.",
    "GNN-RAG improves performance on multihop questions (≥2 hops) by 6.5-11.8% F1 points over RoG.",
    "Furthermore, RA improves performance on single-hop questions by 0.8-2.6% F1 points over GNN-RAG.",
    "Table 10 presents results with respect to the number of correct answers."
  ]
}